-- GM bonds rally after company files for bankruptcy
-- 
-- Mon Jun 1, 2009 8:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/06/01/us-gm-bonds-sb-idUSTRE5502O320090601

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The debt of General Motors Corp. rallied early on Monday after court documents showed the company had filed for bankruptcy protection. 

 GM's benchmark 8.375 percent bonds due in July 2033 last traded at 13 cents on the dollar, up from 10.5 cents on the dollar late Friday, according to MarketAxess. (Reporting by  John Parry ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)